HEADWORD: Throatboll
<hw>Throat"boll`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Throat</ets> + <ets>boll</ets> a ball.]</ety> <def>The Adam's
apple in the neck.</def> <mark>[Obs. or R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By the <qex>throatboll</qex> he caught Aleyn.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

